WILSHIRE OIL COMPANY et al., Appellants, v. UNITED STATES of America et al., Appellees. No. 7764. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 3, 1935. For opinion below, see 9 F. Supp. 396. Robert B. Murphey, Alex W. Davis, Wm. L. Murphey, and Ralph F. Forch, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellants. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Clyde Thomas, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellees.

Before WILBUR and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges, and ST. SURE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellants and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeals herein dismissed and mandate issued forthwith.
